## 🧭 What is the Three-Sutra Theory?

The Three-Sutra Theory proposes that any complex system—from an individual to a civilization—can be understood and optimized through three fundamental, orthogonal dimensions:

| Dimension | Three-Sutra | Digital Expression | Tao Te Ching Mapping |
|-----------|-------------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **Structure** | Space Sutra (空弦 Φ) | 000 Zero-Point State | Tao (The Way) |
| **Process** | Time Sutra (时弦 Τ)  | 666 Holographic State | De (Virtue/Power) |
| **Consciousness**| Mind Sutra (心弦 Ψ) | Tri-Question Switching | Fa (Law/Method) |

**Core Formula: The Resonance Coefficient R**
\[
R = \frac{3\sqrt[3]{\Psi \cdot \Phi \cdot \Tau}}{|\Psi-\Phi| + |\Phi-\Tau| + |\Tau-\Psi| + \epsilon}
\]
A higher R value indicates a healthier, more harmonious, and "Tao-aligned" system.

